The paper deals with autonomous navigation of micro aerial vehicles, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The approach proposed in the paper involves the use of convolutional networks for predicting gate poses, which is a computer vision task (cs.CV). The incorporation of uncertainty in the gate pose estimates and the use of model predictive control suggest the use of machine learning techniques (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the control and optimization of a dynamic system, which falls under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
